<body>
    <form id="form1" runat="server">
    <div>
    <table style="width:100%;" border="1">
        <tr>
            <td colspan="4" class="dpGreenHeader12">
                NON-PRODUCTIVE DESCRIPTIONS
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>A</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>LEADERSHIP SKILLS</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>
                1
            </td>
            <td>
                Written Communication
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to communicate through writing to sub-ordinates, superiors, customers in such a way that it is understandable to the recipient.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                2
            </td>
            <td>
                Oral Communication
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to communicate verbally
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                3
            </td>
            <td>
               Team Building
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should monitor the team performance on regular basis, asses the team, provide them with regular feedbacks, identify the training needs required for individual operators, organise training sessions, fine tune the operators, communicate the information down the line in a proper manner for the welfare of the team and company
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                4
            </td>
            <td>
                Assigning Responsibilities
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Identify proper person in a team and asses their strength and allot responsibilities for them 
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                5
            </td>
            <td>
                Decision Making
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be strong in knowing and analysing the expectation of the position/client handled and able to decide
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                6
            </td>
            <td>
                Problem Solving
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be technically strong in solving the issues related to job and other man management issues in the team
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                7
            </td>
            <td>
                Production Planning and Allocation
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should properly analyse the job on arrival, plan such that files are delivered ahead or on time with 100% quality
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                8
            </td>
            <td>
                Change Management
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to adhere to the process, procedure change or role change assigned by the Management
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                9
            </td>
            <td>
                Quality Management
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be accountable to the quality of the output of the team, should follow the existing and also come out with new strategies like process improvement, tool updates, new tool implementation for ensuring quality
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                10
            </td>
            <td>
                MIS Management
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should ensure all jobs coming and flowing are properly booked-in MIS and billed to customer
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
               11
            </td>
            <td>
                Production / Job Tracking
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should maintain production tracking sheet and have records of all jobs processed and have a review of them on a daily basis
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>B</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>ATTITUDE</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                12
            </td>
            <td>
                Flexible & Adaptable
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should be flexible to the jobs assigned, responsibilities or additional tasks given or any request raised <br />
                * Should get accustomed to the new role given to them and provide their best to the assigned responsibility
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                13
            </td>
            <td>
                Relationship with Managers / Colleagues
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have a smooth relationship with superiors and colleagues and having healthy arugements by avoiding non-productive/unnecessary arguments with superiors and colleagues
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                14
            </td>
            <td>
                Self Initiative, Process Improvement, Team Participation
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should take initiatives for the goodness of the job and company<br />
* Should be able to provide valuable points required to the development of the process<br />
* Should be an effective participant in all activities organised by the company and the commitment to the success of the team as a whole
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                15
            </td>
            <td>
                Response to Comments</td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have a positive approach on feedbacks given by Superiors and taking appropriate steps on the comments
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>C</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>GENERAL</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                16
            </td>
            <td>
                Job Knowledge & Technical Expertise
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should have good knowledge about the process and work done and the requirements of the clients working<br />
                *Should have good technical knowledge to solve any unexpected error occurring during work, raise it to the superiors and should not be others-dependent always
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                17
            </td>
            <td>
                Knowledge Transfer
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to serve as Mentor and transfer their work knowledge for the welfare of the team and company to the colleagues with superior knowledge
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                18
            </td>
            <td>
                Work place Ethics & Adherence to Policies
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should restrict unwanted wandering in the production floor, unnecessary talking or standing in places other than their own, should behave gently with colleagues, avoid unnecessary quarrels<br />
                * Should follow proper dress code, display ID cards, adhere to instructions and procedures and policies of the company
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>D</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>ATTENDANCE</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                19
            </td>
            <td>
                Leave Management
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to inform, plan their leaves in advance ensuring there is no excess leaves taken other than allotted and work not affected. Values will differs for uninformed leaves, using their allotted leaves, having leave balance in their accounts. 
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                20
            </td>
            <td>
                Punctuality
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be present in the system in adherence to the shift timings allotted to them, take breaks within the allotted time
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    </div>
    </form>
